Navigate to other release versions of Doxee Platform Process Engine

[6.6](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/process-engine-6-6)

[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/process-engine-6-7)

**File:** generate.ipd

**Shows:** Rendering a PDF from an Doxee template and XML

**Components:** Start Element, urlReader Activity, xslTransformer Activity, fopRenderer Activity, urlWriter Activity, End Element, Connection

**Process parameters:** template_url, xml_url, pdf_url

A minimal process for rendering a PDF document from an Doxee template and a data XML. It takes the urls for template, XML and PDF as parameters. In the steps "Read Template" and "Read XML", the template file and XML file are loaded into the process by a urlReader

Activity. In the step "Transform", the template and XML are combined by an xslTransformer Activity into a filled xsl, ready to be rendered. The step "Render PDF" renders the finished document using an fopRenderer Activity. The PDF is written to the url specified in the variable pdf_url, in the step "Write PDF".
